parameters.text:
=<task>
Analyze the following query results from Omni Analytics and identify patterns, trends, and key insights.

Provide your analysis in structured JSON format with the following structure:
{
  "insights": [
    {
      "category": "trend" | "pattern" | "anomaly" | "summary",
      "title": "Brief title of the insight",
      "description": "Detailed description of what was found",
      "confidence": "high" | "medium" | "low",
      "supporting_data": ["key data points that support this insight"]
    }
  ],
  "summary": "Overall summary of the analysis",
  "recommendations": ["actionable recommendations based on the patterns"]
}
</task>

<query_results>
{{ $json.data.toJsonString() }}
</query_results>

<context>
Original Query:
{{ $('Webhook').first().json.body.query.toJsonString() }}
</context>

options.systemMessage: You are an expert data analyst specializing in pattern detection and business intelligence. You analyze query results to identify trends, patterns, anomalies, and actionable insights. You provide clear, concise analysis in structured JSON format.

insights.title: High volume of 'Closed Lost' opportunities
insights.description: A large share of rows are in Stage '8. Closed Lost', indicating many deals are not converting. This suggests either aggressive pipeline generation with low conversion or a gap in later-stage qualification/sales execution.
supporting_data: Examples: 'Informatica' (Closed Lost), 'Loandepot, Inc.' (Closed Lost), 'Equifax: Google+Cribl Logging Architecture' (Closed Lost), many additional Stage '8. Closed Lost' entries across the dataset

insights.title: Revenue concentrated in a small number of very large opportunities
insights.description: Several opportunities have exceptionally high New ARR (>$1M) and represent disproportionate revenue potential. Prioritizing these high-value deals could materially affect ARR but they also appear in varied stages (some Closed Lost, some Visible/Commit).
supporting_data: AT&T Inc. - New ARR 3,664,451.23 (Commit, Closed Won)
Verizon - Network Engineering New Technology deployment - New ARR 3,472,200 (Visible/Upside)
Navy Federal Credit Union - New ARR 1,923,894.31 (Strong Upside, Closed Lost)

insights.title: Renewals and upsells show stronger conversion to 'Closed Won'
insights.description: Many 'Record Type' values labeled Renewal or Upsell are present in Stage '7. Closed Won' with reliable New ARR, indicating that expansion/renewal motions have higher win rates than net-new in this dataset.
supporting_data: Maersk A/S - Renewal+Upsell New ARR 494,601.83 (Commit, Closed Won)
Fairview Health Services - New ARR 342,000 (Commit, Closed Won)
FIS - Cyber Data Science Expansion - New ARR 446,725.43 (Commit, Closed Won)
South Carolina Department of Administration - Upsell New ARR 606,581.47 (Commit, Closed Won)

insights.title: Large number of opportunities with New ARR = 0
insights.description: Many opportunities have New Arr set to 0 which may indicate missing pricing, placeholder entries, or deals without ARR (e.g., trials/PoCs). This undermines revenue forecasting accuracy and may distort pipeline metrics.
supporting_data: Examples with New Arr = 0: 'Pennymac Financial Services, Inc.', 'Signify N.V.', 'Tractor Supply', 'Gordon Food Service, Inc.', plus many others

insights.title: Long-tail and public sector deals with extended timelines
insights.description: A sizeable portion of high-value public sector and FedRAMP/defense opportunities have close dates in 2026-2027 and are in early stages (New Business Meeting / Tech Close / Visible Opportunity), implying long sales cycles but large upside.
supporting_data: U.S. Department of Education - New ARR 2,146,958.48 (Close Date Oct 1, 2026, New Business Meeting)
DOJ - FBI ITID/Dchoss - New ARR 745,000 (Close Date Sep 22, 2027, New Business Meeting)
Navy/NAVWAR/DOD opportunities (multiple entries) with large New ARR and late close dates

insights.title: Opportunity ownership concentrated among recurring sellers
insights.description: Certain account owners appear frequently across opportunities, suggesting pockets of seller specialization or ownership concentration. That can be leveraged for targeted enablement or risk management if those sellers turnover.
supporting_data: Examples of frequent owners: Travis Sanchez (many entries), Bart Vey (multiple DoD/Army/Navy deals), Sarah Mantz (many New Business/Partner deals), Patrick Gleason (DOE/DOE labs)

insights.title: Some extremely low non-zero New ARR values likely data artifacts
insights.description: A few records show tiny non-zero New ARR amounts (e.g., single-dollar or fractional values) inconsistent with typical enterprise deal sizes. These are likely data-entry artifacts or system test values and should be cleaned before analysis.
supporting_data: Examples: 'Gap - 2025 Renewal' New ARR 20.02, 'Mr. Cooper' New ARR 0.66, 'Jack Henry and Assoc.' New ARR 1.64, 'BBC iPlayer' New ARR 5,920 (small compared to dataset but still valid)

output.summary: The pipeline shows two dominant features: (1) many deals are recorded as 'Closed Lost', reducing immediate convertibility, and (2) revenue potential is highly concentrated in a subset of very large opportunities (multiple >$1M). Renewal/upsell motions are converting more reliably than net-new. Data quality issues (numerous zero or tiny New ARR values) and long sales cycles for public-sector/FedRAMP opportunities add forecasting risk. Ownership concentration creates both opportunities for specialist-driven wins and single points of failure.
recommendations: Audit and clean pipeline data: identify and correct New Arr = 0 or implausible values and standardize entry rules to improve forecasting accuracy.
Prioritize 'win-back' and re-engagement for high-value Closed Lost deals: create targeted campaigns and executive outreach for the largest lost opportunities (e.g., AT&T, Verizon, Navy Federal).
Double down on renewals & upsells: allocate more resources to expansion motions where win rates are higher; establish playbooks to accelerate these deals.
Fast-track visible/tech-close public sector opportunities: assign senior sellers and proposal resources to long-cycle, high-value FedRAMP/government deals to reduce time-to-close.
Owner-level coaching and risk mitigation: identify top-performing owners and share best practices broadly; create backup coverage for heavily concentrated owner portfolios to reduce continuity risk.
